<div id="review_2661091759" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2661091759" />
    <a title="Adrian" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22809267-adrian"><img alt="Adrian" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1484242635p2/22809267.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2661091759?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adrian" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adrian" href="/user/show/22809267-adrian">Adrian</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061003691" href="/book/show/1786571.Death_on_the_Nile">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22809267-adrian?shelf=det-agatha-christie">det-agatha-christie</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22809267-adrian?shelf=zz-owned-books">zz-owned-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22809267-adrian?shelf=detectives-challenge-hp-2018-20">detectives-challenge-hp-2018-20</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2661091759" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2012065801896040382">I WILL review tonight, honest 😬<br/><br/>So here is tonight, and here is my review. I&apos;m obviously still not fully up to speed as I don&apos;t normally take this long to write a review, especially for a Poirot and for a book I liked. Nor do I normally read my monthly Poirot so late in the month<br/>Now I cannot ever remember reading this book, that said I of course know the story having seen Ustinov, Suchet and Finney all mooch around the boat to differing extents and pounce on red herrings or red stoles to bring th</span>
  <span id="freeText2012065801896040382" style="display:none">I WILL review tonight, honest 😬<br /><br />So here is tonight, and here is my review. I'm obviously still not fully up to speed as I don't normally take this long to write a review, especially for a Poirot and for a book I liked. Nor do I normally read my monthly Poirot so late in the month<br />Now I cannot ever remember reading this book, that said I of course know the story having seen Ustinov, Suchet and Finney all mooch around the boat to differing extents and pounce on red herrings or red stoles to bring the case to a conclusion.<br />Now having seen all those film/tv versions, was the book the same, different, better or worse ? Well I think it was a good Poirot novel and in some ways was different and better than all the visual versions to date (Kenneth Branagh has a new version next year, hmm !! ).<br />The story is , as ever for Christie, convoluted and very clever, if you haven't seen or read the novel, then I will not spoil it for you, suffice to say I defy you to guess the murderer, before Poirot starts giving out obvious clues.<br />So why wasn't it 5 stars, well I suppose because I knew the outcome from the movies (oh so many times) and so it wasn't as new or fresh to me as I would have liked. That said parts were new as I have never read the book, and so it was a solid 4 stars.<br />This is part of the Detectives Group buddy read of every Poirot at the rate of one a month, so we still have over a year to go, which i am really looking forward to.</span>
