<div id="review_1355586556" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1355586556" />
    <a title="Ginger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14097149-ginger"><img alt="Ginger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1593449448p2/14097149.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1355586556?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ginger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ginger" href="/user/show/14097149-ginger">Ginger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/54110717-death-on-the-nile">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=2021-mount-tbr">2021-mount-tbr</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1355586556" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13559791962473423035"><b>It’s always fun to get back into the mind of <u>Agatha Christie</u>.<br/>And what a meticulous and creative mind she has!</b><br/><br/>I haven’t had the chance to read <b>Death on the Nile</b> and I saw it would be a movie this year.<br/>I thought, “I need to finally read this book before I watch the movie!”<br/><br/>Because as most of us bibliophiles now,<br/><u>Book first then movie! This is the way. 🤣😂</u><br/><br/>I thought the mystery and details of the death of our main character, Linnet Ridgeway was well done.<br/>I had a feeling it might go this way, but I wasn</span>
  <span id="freeText13559791962473423035" style="display:none"><b>It’s always fun to get back into the mind of <u>Agatha Christie</u>.<br />And what a meticulous and creative mind she has!</b><br /><br />I haven’t had the chance to read <b>Death on the Nile</b> and I saw it would be a movie this year.<br />I thought, “I need to finally read this book before I watch the movie!”<br /><br />Because as most of us bibliophiles now,<br /><u>Book first then movie! This is the way. 🤣😂</u><br /><br />I thought the mystery and details of the death of our main character, Linnet Ridgeway was well done.<br />I had a feeling it might go this way, but I wasn’t sure on the details of the death.<br />And it’s a complicated one!<br /><br />Of course, I distrusted everyone on the cruise, so I wasn’t shocked.<br />In fact, Hercule Poirot almost got played in this one and his little gray cells were slipping!<br /><br />I also liked the reveals of the other mysteries involving characters on the cruise. They were well done and elaborate.<br />I liked all the dirty little secrets that the passengers had that were onboard on the cruise.<br />I laughed at a few such as <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[…<br /><br />✔️ The old, mean and secretive alcoholic lady<br />✔️ The old, mean and kleptomaniac lady<br /> ⬆️⬆️⬆️ <u>(notice a pattern here)</u> 🤣<br />✔️ The rich guy that’s undercover as a poor and angry man.<br />✔️ The secretive arms dealer that’s someone else.<br /><br />and much more!  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />The great thing with <u>Christie</u> books is no one is ever what they seem, and everyone has their secrets! I really love that in her books.<br /><br /><b>Definitely get to this one if you enjoy murder mysteries and love books by <u>Agatha Christie</u>.<br />I was not disappointed and definitely entertained by how it all played out!</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="13559791962473423035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


