<span id="freeTextContainer1934417984891991071">Choose Your Own Adventure!<br/><br/>You are a poor sap who loves an English rose, a jewel of society, a gateway to fortune and romance. Together you travel the exotic Nile, surrounded by jealousy and greed and yearned-for vengeance, each of your fellow passengers a bizarre and unsettling caricature, each one morbidly following your every move. Murder strikes – not once, not twice, but thrice! The situation becomes quite unbearable, and made worse by the attentions of a notorious Belgian muckraker. How do </span>
  <span id="freeText1934417984891991071" style="display:none">Choose Your Own Adventure!<br /><br />You are a poor sap who loves an English rose, a jewel of society, a gateway to fortune and romance. Together you travel the exotic Nile, surrounded by jealousy and greed and yearned-for vengeance, each of your fellow passengers a bizarre and unsettling caricature, each one morbidly following your every move. Murder strikes – not once, not twice, but thrice! The situation becomes quite unbearable, and made worse by the attentions of a notorious Belgian muckraker. How do you get out of this byzantine mess? Whatever is an English lad to do?<br /><br />If you decide that Egypt is for savages and you’d prefer to get your jollies at a posh resort on the southern coast of England, choose <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/134199450">http://www.goodreads.com/review/show/...</a><br /><br />If you decide that Egyptian culture is worthy of further study, choose <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/134199611">http://www.goodreads.com/review/show/...</a></span>
