        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3597089409" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5829791071424956080">3.5-4****<br/><br/>I did prefer “The murder on the Orient Express” hence the slightly lower rating. However, in true Christie style, she introduces a bunch of different characters, each with their own secrets and connections; The genius of Hercule Poirot; And many twists and turns and unravellings which are a marvel to read. <br/><br/>She always keeps me guessing as to the truth behind the crime and the characters, and it’s addictive to keep turning the pages to see what happens.</span>

